> Who doesn't love a family-style fajita night? You'll fill warm tortillas with slices
> of paprika-spiced bavette steak and sautéed onion and bell pepper. Creamy
> refried beans and cilantro-lime rice round out the feast, while toppings like
> guacamole, sour cream, and pickled jalapeño allow everyone to create their own
> perfect plate.

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
@water{1 1/4%cups}, @turmeric{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> For 4 servings: use 2 1/4 cups water and 1/2 tsp turmeric.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Fajita Prep ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons,
removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

Zest and quarter @lime{2}.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP
(2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. On a separate #cutting board{},
thinly slice. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}; combine with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{drizzle}, @savory paprika blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Set aside until ready to use.

== Pickled Jalapeño ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced jalapeño,
@sugar{1/2%tsp}, juice from two lime wedges, and a pinch of salt.
Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until jalapeño is tender,
~{30-60%seconds}. Refrigerate until ready to use.

> For 4 servings: use 1 tsp sugar and juice from four lime wedges.

== Pickled Onion ==

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, half the cilantro,
juice from two lime wedges, and a pinch of salt. Cover with plastic wrap
and refrigerate until ready to use.

> For 4 servings: use four lime wedges.

== Refried Beans ==

Heat @refried black beans{16%ounce} in a second small pot over medium-high heat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until warmed through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Fajita Veggies and Steak ==

While beans cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add sliced onion and bell pepper; season with salt and pepper. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat;
transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked to desired doneness,
~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from heat.

== Warm Tortillas ==

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, remaining cilantro, and as
much lime zest as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> For 4 servings: use 2 TBSP butter.

Serve rice, steak, fajita veggies, beans, tortillas, @sour cream{3%tbsp},
@guacamole{4%tbsp}, marinated onion, pickled jalapeños, and any remaining lime
wedges family style so everyone can make their own fajitas.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.